The '''Imperial Executive Building''',<ref name="Dark Lord 12">[[Darth Vader (2017) 12|''Darth Vader'' (2017) 12]]</ref> also known as the '''Senate Office Building''',<ref name="UltimateSW">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref> was a dome-shaped office building located near the [[Imperial Senate Building]] on the [[planet]] [[Coruscant]].<ref name="RotS">{{Film|III}}</ref> It was also referred to as the '''Republic executive building''' or the '''Senate executive building''' during the [[time]] of the [[Galactic Republic]].<ref name="ZBSBepguide">{{SW|url=series/clone-wars/the-zillo-beast-strikes-back-episode-guide|text="The Zillo Beast Strikes Back" Episode Guide &#124; The Clone Wars}}</ref> The executive building contained offices for [[Senator|members]] of the [[Galactic Senate]],<ref name="UltimateSW" /> as well as the [[Emperor's office|office]] of [[Supreme Chancellor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]].<ref name="AotC" /> A number of landing bays were located at the upper levels of the building.<ref name="RotS" />

During the [[Clone Wars]], Chancellor Palpatine directed the Republic's [[Republic Military|military]] efforts from the executive building. When the [[Jedi Order]] discovered Palpatine's true identity as the [[Sith Lord]] [[Darth]] Sidious, four [[Jedi Master]]s, [[Mace Windu]], [[Kit Fisto]], [[Saesee Tiin]], and [[Agen Kolar]], attempted to arrest him in his office. Palpatine engaged them in a [[lightsaber]] [[Duel in Palpatine's office|duel]], [[Death|killing]] three [[Jedi]] before Windu ultimately overpowered him. However, before Windu could strike the killing blow, [[Jedi Knight]] [[Anakin Skywalker]] stormed into the Chancellor's office and demanded that Palpatine be [[Prisoner|taken]] alive, believing Palpatine had the power keep Skywalker's wife, [[Padmé Amidala]], alive. Windu asserted that Palpatine was too dangerous to live, but Skywalker severed Windu's [[Limb|arm]], allowing Palpatine to attack him with [[Force lightning]], blasting him through the window and sending him falling to his [[death]]. With Windu's demise and Skywalker's fall to the [[dark side of the Force]], Sidious issued [[Order 66]] to the [[clone trooper]]s of the [[Grand Army of the Republic]] from the executive building, declaring all Jedi enemies of the state.<ref name="RotS" />

